{"id": "7646ad6a-6caf-4ec5-90d0-53a4de0d2844", "slug": "something-new-in-tuindorp-oostzaan", "title": "Something New in Tuindorp Oostzaan", "type": "review", "status": "published", "excerpt": "Het Wilde Wat performs Iets Nieuws Onder de Zon", "body": "<p>This weekend I killed two birds with one stone: I got to see my friend’s choir perform, and I finally got inside a building that has always sparked my curiosity. What appears to be an abandoned barn nestled amongst the trees in Tuindorp Oostzaan is actually a reclaimed church-turned-event space: JoyJoyJoy Basilika. Het Wilde Wat performed their summer concert there, titled <em>Iets Nieuws Onder de Zon </em>(Something New Under the Sun). The 10m-high vaulted ceilings, raw exposed brick, and the massive, semi-circular arched alcove created the perfect architectural combination for the harmonies to echo throughout. </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!DCAe!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8a41f0a-2157-4f36-88c2-9874b9619bcb_3264x2448.jpeg\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!DCAe!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8a41f0a-2157-4f36-88c2-9874b9619bcb_3264x2448.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!DCAe!,w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8a41f0a-2157-4f36-88c2-9874b9619bcb_3264x2448.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!DCAe!,w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8a41f0a-2157-4f36-88c2-9874b9619bcb_3264x2448.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!DCAe!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8a41f0a-2157-4f36-88c2-9874b9619bcb_3264x2448.jpeg 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!DCAe!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8a41f0a-2157-4f36-88c2-9874b9619bcb_3264x2448.jpeg\" width=\"521\" height=\"390.75\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/e8a41f0a-2157-4f36-88c2-9874b9619bcb_3264x2448.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1092,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:521,&quot;bytes&quot;:1765199,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://clairesculturaldispatch.substack.com/i/201120765?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8a41f0a-2157-4f36-88c2-9874b9619bcb_3264x2448.jpeg&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!DCAe!,w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8a41f0a-2157-4f36-88c2-9874b9619bcb_3264x2448.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!DCAe!,w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8a41f0a-2157-4f36-88c2-9874b9619bcb_3264x2448.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!DCAe!,w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8a41f0a-2157-4f36-88c2-9874b9619bcb_3264x2448.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!DCAe!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fe8a41f0a-2157-4f36-88c2-9874b9619bcb_3264x2448.jpeg 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture><div class=\"image-link-expand\"><div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\"><svg role=\"img\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a><figcaption class=\"image-caption\">The unassuming exterior of JoyJoyJoy Basilika.</figcaption></figure></div><p>The repertoire was an ambitious mix of modern and traditional folk alongside Gregorian chants. All united by a theme of spirituality and transcendence. The choirs forty or so voices blended the altos, sopranos, tenors and basses in perfect balance. No instruments required. One of my favourite pieces was <em>There Are Some Men</em> by Philip Glass; the choir's perfectly controlled dynamics, from pianissimo to forte, conveyed an extraordinary emotional range. I also loved <em>O Radiant Dawn</em> by James MacMillan (a fellow Scot). The harmonies of the whole choir singing together were beautiful, and we were even treated to a little extra during the encore. They also sang Kaval Sviri, a traditional Bulgarian folk song. An insider Bulgarian friend says this would have been particularly challenging due to its complex rhythms. On top of that, they also sang in five or six different languages throughout the performance. Het Wilde Wat really were demonstrating their talents and versatility.</p><p>The concert was exceptionally good value (Davide, you need to increase your prices). The only challenge came during the quieter moments, when the choir found itself competing with a handful of tiny audience members who seemed determined to contribute their own noises.</p><p><em>Seen at JoyJoyJoy Basilika, Amsterdam, Saturday 6th June 2026</em></p>", "related_event_urls": ["9fc5a983-a325-5d59-9316-c2d5445b2d82"], "created_at": "2026-06-08T14:20:49.861000", "updated_at": "2026-06-23T18:52:36.192222"}